items.name: Amarberry
items.description: This yellow berry is exceptionally juicy, providing significant hydration and a small amount of nourishment.

items.name: Amarberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Amarberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Azulberry
items.description: This curious blue berry has a gel-like interior, providing significant hydration. Curiously, it also seems to saturate the blood with oxygen almost instantaneously, but can lead to a mild to severe stupor if overeaten.

items.name: Azulberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Azulberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Citronal Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Citronal crop.  Can be planted in Medium or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Citronal
items.description:
This citrus fruit provides significant hydration and a small boost to energy, along with a moderate amount of nutrition, making it ideal for situations in hot temperatures with scarce water sources.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptional hydrating properties of this fruit provides lasting relief, quenching thirst for 30 seconds.</>

items.name: Cocodrupe Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Cocodrupe tree.  Can be planted in Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Cocodrupe
items.description:
<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">Unopened: 4 Uses Remain</>

This valuable drupe provides significant hydration and a small boost to energy, along with a moderate amount of nutrition, making it ideal for situations in hot temperatures with scarce water sources. May be used in place of citronal.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptional hydrating properties of this fruit provides lasting relief, quenching thirst for 30 seconds. Unopened, the cocodrupe will not spoil quickly. May be consumed up to four times.</>

items.name: Cocodrupe (Opened)
items.description:
<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">Opened: 3 Uses Remain</>

This valuable drupe provides significant hydration and a small boost to energy, along with a moderate amount of nutrition, making it ideal for situations in hot temperatures with scarce water sources. May be used in place of citronal.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptional hydrating properties of this fruit provides lasting relief, quenching thirst for 30 seconds.</>

items.name: Cocodrupe (Opened)
items.description:
<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">Opened: 2 Uses Remain</>

This valuable drupe provides significant hydration and a small boost to energy, along with a moderate amount of nutrition, making it ideal for situations in hot temperatures with scarce water sources. May be used in place of citronal.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptional hydrating properties of this fruit provides lasting relief, quenching thirst for 30 seconds.</>

items.name: Cocodrupe (Opened)
items.description:
<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">Opened: 1 Use Remains</>

This valuable drupe provides significant hydration and a small boost to energy, along with a moderate amount of nutrition, making it ideal for situations in hot temperatures with scarce water sources. May be used in place of citronal.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptional hydrating properties of this fruit provides lasting relief, quenching thirst for 30 seconds.</>

items.name: Eaten Cocodrupe
items.description: It looks as though this coconut has been opened and its contents eaten. Tear the husk off to get to the valuable drupe seed or wait for the outer husk to decompose.

items.name: Longrass Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Longrass crop.  Can be planted in Medium or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Longrass
items.description:
This grain plant provides a balanced degree of nutrition and hydration, along with a small boost to energy, making it ideal for use when crafting or hunting a dangerous predator.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptionally rich mineral content of the juicy kernals naturally enhances cognitive function, increasing the rate of learning for 30 seconds.</>

items.name: Mejoberry
items.description: This wild berry is exceptionally delicious and juicy, providing a significant source of nourishment and hydration.

items.name: Mejoberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Mejoberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Narcoberry
items.description: This fairly common black berry induces a restless sleep, providing some nourishment, and some healing benefits.

items.name: Narcoberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Narcoberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Cactus Sap
items.description: Cut of cactus that giving sap and when it is consumed hydrates your body

items.name: Narrowleaf Seeds
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Narrowleaf plant.  Can be planted in Large Crop Plots. Slow growing, Narrowleaf produces an excess of cactus sap that can be harvested regularly. The plant also attracts a number of small moths, using the mature plant to lay their eggs, providing small amounts of harvestable silk.

items.name: Pumpigourd Seeds
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Pumpigourd vine.  Can be planted in Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Pumpigourd
items.description:
This large gourd provides massive nutrition and a small boost to energy, all while promoting natural healing, making it ideal for long journeys filled with dangers. May replace Rockarrot in any recipe.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptional nutritional value and rich vitamin contents of this gourd provides a boost to healing temporarily, soothing even some of the worst wounds for both humans and their dinosaur companions.</>

items.name: Giant Pumpigourd
items.description:
This GIANT gourd provides massive nutrition and a significant boost to energy, all while promoting natural healing, making it ideal for long journeys filled with dangers.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptional nutritional value and rich vitamin contents of this gourd provides a boost to healing temporarily, soothing even some of the worst wounds for both humans and their dinosaur companions.</>

items.name: Rockarrot Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Rockarrot crop.  Can be planted in Medium or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Rockarrot
items.description:
This root vegetable provides a moderate amount of nutrition, but a significant boost to energy, making it ideal during stamina draining activities, such as mining, harvesting, or even swimming.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The energizing nutrients of this woody root greatly helps with mental acuity and focus, boosting stamina regeneration for 30 seconds.</>

items.name: Savoroot Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Savoroot crop.  Can be planted in Medium or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Savoroot
items.description:
This starchy tuber is exceptionally nutritious, making it ideal for lowering the demand for food over time, particularly in hungry herbivores.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The high fiber content of the starch tuber naturally promotes fullness, reducing the need to eat for 30 seconds.</>

items.name: Stimberry

items.name: Maggot Bandages
items.description: Maggots eat away rotting flesh and release antimicrobial residue, helping to heal slowly over time.

items.name: Blood Pack
items.description: Extracted human blood, which can be used to restore health over time if consumed.

items.name: Concentrated Hemoglobin
items.description: A pack of concentrated hemoglobin enriched with hyperoxygenated fructose from azulberries and stimulant. Slows oxygen use while underwater.

items.name: Narcotic
items.description: Increases your health, but puts you to sleep.

items.name: Stimulant
items.description: This tart and energizing brew can also serve as an effective, emergency antitoxin.

items.name: Cooked Lamb Chop
items.description:
Cooked mutton from an ovis, provides significant nourishment, and a large boost in energy and health benefits.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptionally rich protein content of the meat promotes moderate natural healing for 30 seconds.</>

items.name: Cooked Meat
items.description: Cooked meat from a terrestrial animal, provides significant nourishment, along with a small boost in energy and health benefits.

items.name: Cooked Fish Meat
items.description: Cooked meat from an aquatic animal, provides some nourishment and health benefits, along with a significant boost in energy.

items.name: Cooked Meat Jerky
items.description:
Sates your hunger, and provides health while being digested.  Lasts longer than cooked meat.
Wild carnivores will eat it, but prefer raw meat.

items.name: Cooked Prime Meat
items.description:
This cooked piece of delicious tenderloin is a massive source of nutrition and energy.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptionally rich protein content of the meat promotes moderate natural healing for 30 seconds.</>

items.name: Cooked Prime Fish Meat
items.description:
Delicious cooked meat from an aquatic animal, providing significant nourishment, along with a large boost in energy and health benefits.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptionally rich protein content of the meat promotes significant natural healing for 30 seconds.</>

items.name: Prime Meat Jerky
items.description:
Sates your hunger, and provides health while being digested.  More effective than normal meat jerky, and lasts longer than cooked prime meat.
Wild carnivores like this meat a lot.

items.name: Raw Meat
items.description: Eating raw food will sate hunger, but is unhealthy for humans.  Most wild carnivores prefer raw meat to cooked meat.

items.name: Raw Fish Meat
items.description: This cut of fish meat can be eaten raw safely or cooked for further nutritional and health benefits.

items.name: Raw Mutton
items.description: Eating raw food will sate hunger, but is unhealthy for humans.  This excellent cut spoils very quickly.

items.name: Raw Prime Meat
items.description: Eating raw food will sate hunger, but is unhealthy for humans.  This excellent cut spoils very quickly.

items.name: Raw Prime Fish Meat
items.description:
This delicious slice of fish meat can be eaten raw safely or cooked for significant nutritional and health benefits.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">The exceptionally rich protein content of the meat promotes significant natural healing for 30 seconds.</>

items.description:
Eww... do not eat.
This must have a use, right?

items.name: Basic Kibble
items.description: This pet food recipe has been carefully designed to give balanced nutrition to many smaller creatures. Humans have difficulty digesting this.

items.name: Simple Kibble
items.description: This pet food recipe has been carefully designed to give balanced nutrition to many small creatures. Humans have difficulty digesting this.

items.name: Regular Kibble
items.description: This specially blended pet food is a favorite of many medium creatures. Containing only the finest natural ingredients, it provides pets with the balanced nutrition they need. And with a taste they can't resist, they'll warm up to you in no time! Not intended for human consumption.

items.name: Superior Kibble
items.description: This specially blended pet food is a favorite of many larger creatures. Containing only the finest natural ingredients, it provides pets with the balanced nutrition they need. And with a taste they can't resist, they'll warm up to you in no time! Not intended for human consumption.

items.name: Exceptional Kibble
items.description: This specially blended pet food is a favorite of many extra large creatures. Containing only the finest natural ingredients, it provides pets with the balanced nutrition they need. And with a taste they can't resist, they'll warm up to you in no time! Not intended for human consumption.

items.name: Extraordinary Kibble
items.description: This specially blended pet food is a favorite of many exotic creatures. Containing only the finest natural ingredients, it provides pets with the balanced nutrition they need. And with a taste they can't resist, they'll warm up to you in no time! Not intended for human consumption.

items.name: Fertilizer
items.description: High nitrogen fertilizer that helps crops grow in their plots.

items.name: Sinew Fiber
items.description: Fibrous bands of tissues harvested from the large tendons of animals. May be used in place of plant fiber.

items.name: Straw Fodder
items.description: This mix of thatch and plant fibers can be consumed by large herbivores.

items.name: Armored Plates
items.description: Harvested hide from an armored animal, with thick, boney scutes and plates making it highly resistant to damage. Due to the silica-rich nature of the plates, it can be used in place of Silica Pearls.

items.name: Chitin
items.description: This firm, flexible material makes up exoskeletons. Hacked primarily from dead insects.

items.name: Clay
items.description: Created by grinding Sand with Cactus Sap in a Mortar and Pestle.

items.name: Coir Fiber
items.description: Tough and hardened cocodrupe husk fibers woven into salt-resistant cords. May be used in place of plant or sinew fiber.

items.name: Condensed Gas
items.description: A highly concentrated and hardened gas deposit. This could be refined back into it's gaseous form.

items.name: Feathers
items.description: Plucked from avians and feathered dinosaurs, this resource is essential in the crafting of arrows and providing insulation. It may also be used as a substitute for cactus sap in the creation of clay.

items.name: Plant Fiber
items.description: Delicately collected fibrous strands of plants braided into pliable cords. Slowly decomposes over time.

items.name: Cave Guano
items.description: Cave guano is used to craft gunpowder or can be used as a valuable fertilizer. Will decompose into valuable sulfur over time.

items.name: Gunpowder
items.description: An powerful propellant. Necessary for any firearm or explosive.

items.name: Human Hair
items.description: A lock of human hair!

items.name: Hide
items.description: A thick piece of skin, hacked from a dead animal.

items.name: Ivory Keratin
items.description: A firm, flexible material. Can be found in some animal horns, plates, shells, and ridges.

items.name: Metal
items.description: A lump of unrefined metal ore, mined from rocks usually found high on mountains, or in caves. Can be refined in a Forge.

items.name: Honeycomb Morel
items.description: An exceptionally rare and delicious mushroom, its distinctive sweet and woody taste allows it to be used as a substitute for honey in recipes.

items.name: Oil
items.description: A thick blob of unrefined oil.  Can be refined with hide to make gasoline.

items.name: Fur Pelt
items.description: A thick piece of skin, densely covered with heavy insulating fur. Carefully harvested from a dead animal.

items.name: Organic Polymer
items.description: These incredibly strong, lightweight plates are somehow naturally made in certain creatures. Incredibly hazardous to human health if consumed.

items.name: Quill Hide
items.description: Hide harvested from an animal covered in feathered quill follicles.

items.name: Raw Salt
items.description: Use it to make Preserving Salt!

items.name: Sand
items.description: Used to craft Clay. Can be found in Sand rocks

items.name: Scaled Hide
items.description: Hide harvested from a scaled, terrestrial animal. Can be used in place of quill hide.

items.name: Shagreen Hide
items.description: This highly resilient leather, harvested from an aquatic predator, is difficult to work with. But due to the criss-crossing fibers, it is incredibly strong. Can be used in place of Organic Polymer.

items.name: Silk Fiber
items.description: Obtained from the Moth creatures. Used to craft desert clothes and the tent.

items.name: Cocoon Silk Fiber
items.description: One of the strongest, natural fibers available, this rare silk is found exclusively on egg-laying insects and their nests. May be used in place of silk.

items.name: Stone
items.description: A hefty chunk of stone.

items.name: Sulfur
items.description: Used to craft distinct kind of ammunition. Can be found in the Caves

items.name: Thatch
items.description: Sticks torn from trees.  Useful for primitive bindings.

items.name: Shell Fragment
items.description: A firm, flexible material from the shell of a large animal. Can be used as a replacement for Keratin.

items.name: Wood
items.description: A thick, sturdy cutting from a tree.

items.name: Wool Fiber
items.description: Sheared from a sheep!

items.name: Basic Saddle
items.description: A basic saddle for a relatively passive creature.

items.name: Simple Saddle
items.description: A simple saddle for a relatively docile creature.

items.name: Regular Saddle
items.description: A regular saddle for the Ark's relatively intelligent creatures.

items.name: Superior Saddle
items.description: A superior saddle for the Ark's more formidable creatures.

items.name: Exceptional Saddle
items.description: An exceptional saddle for the Ark's aggressive creatures.

items.name: Extraordinary Saddle
items.description: An extraordinary saddle for the Ark's apex animals.

items.name: Reactivated Zeta Implant
items.description: A reactivated zeta implant. If used concurrently with a basic saddle, it may be programmed to link directly with a relatively passive animal's nervous system and your specimen implant. The result will be a near-telepathic bond, offering unprecendented control over the animal.

items.name: Reactivated Epsilon Implant
items.description: A reactivated epsilon implant. If used concurrently with a simple saddle, it may be programmed to link directly with a relatively docile animal's nervous system and your specimen implant. The result will be a near-telepathic bond, offering unprecendented control over the animal.

items.name: Reactivated Delta Implant
items.description: A reactivated delta implant. If used concurrently with a regular saddle, it may be programmed to link directly with a relatively intelligent animal's nervous system and your specimen implant. The result will be a near-telepathic bond, offering unprecendented control over the animal.

items.name: Reactivated Gamma Implant
items.description: A reactivated gamma implant. If used concurrently with a superior saddle, it may be programmed to link directly with a formidable animal's nervous system and your specimen implant. The result will be a near-telepathic bond, offering unprecendented control over the animal.

items.name: Reactivated Beta Implant
items.description: A reactivated beta implant. If used concurrently with an exceptional saddle, it may be programmed to link directly with even an aggressive animal's nervous system and your specimen implant. The result will be a near-telepathic bond, offering unprecendented control over the animal.

items.name: Reactivated Alpha Implant
items.description: A reactivated alpha implant. If used concurrently with a master saddle, it may be programmed to link directly with the nervous system of some of the Ark's apex animals and your specimen implant. The result will be a near-telepathic bond, offering unprecendented control over the animal.

items.name: Deactivated Zeta Implant
items.description:
The power core of this zeta implant appears damaged, but it may be possible to repair it. With power restored, its interface could be reactivated by introducing a unique DNA sample from a set of preprogrammed organisms. If activated, it could be used to connect with another animal directly through their nervous system.

<RichColor Color="0,1,1,1">Preprogrammed Organism DNA Codes: Human.</>

items.description: Place materials to craft saddles and reactivate implants.

items.name: Living Nest
items.description: A truly exceptional living nest composed of a variety of plants native to the Ark, along with a gargantuan colony of chanterelle mushrooms that requires careful attention and maintenance. Excreting a curious biofilm, when combined with bioluminescent gel found in Anglerfish and other specimens, the subsequent exothermic reaction results in a remarkable substance excellent for incubating even the most sensitive of eggs.

items.name: Bonfire
items.description: Must contain oil to ignite. Once burning, will create a large inferno with choking, black smoke which will repel even the mightiest of predators for a time.

items.name: Campfire
items.description: Perfect for cooking meat, staying warm, and providing light.

items.name: Standing Torch
items.description: A torch on a tall piece of wood that lights and warms the immediate area.

items.name: Compost Bin
items.description: A large bin for converting thatch and dung into high-quality fertilizer.

items.name: Fertilizer (Human)
items.description: High nitrogen fertilizer that helps crops grow in their plots.

items.name: Fertilizer (Small)
items.description: High nitrogen fertilizer that helps crops grow in their plots.

items.name: Fertilizer (Medium)
items.description: High nitrogen fertilizer that helps crops grow in their plots.

items.name: Fertilizer (Large)
items.description: High nitrogen fertilizer that helps crops grow in their plots.

items.name: Fertilizer (Massive)
items.description: High nitrogen fertilizer that helps crops grow in their plots.

items.name: Cooking Pot
items.description: Must contain basic fuel to light the fire.  Put various ingredients with water in this to make soups, stews, and dyes.

items.name: Wooden Foundation
items.description: A foundation is required to build structures in an area.  This one is made from sturdy wood.

items.name: Ember Nest
items.description: A nesting collection of fibrous green plant materials with patches of thatch. Wood embers, warmed by sparkpowder, generate heat to keep Extra Small and Small eggs safely incubating over time. When active, the nest requires regular maintenance.

items.name: Clay Polymer Nest
items.description: A nest made primarily of a clay and organic polymer mixture, exceptionally effective at regulating the temperature for sensitive Medium and Large eggs, regardless of most environmental conditions. When active, the nest requires regular maintenance.

items.name: Tent
items.description: A portable Tent where you can take cover in hostile environments

items.name: Feeding Trough
items.description: Put food for your nearby pets in this, and they'll automatically eat it when hungry!

items.name: Explosive Arrow
items.description: Laced with gunpowder and oil, this arrow packs a punch. Terrible shot? Don't worry, the impact of this arrow will cause some damage to those around.

items.name: Glass Arrow
items.description: This hand-carved obsidian arrowhead is made from volcanic glass which will pierce the skin of your victims causing them to slowly bleed out.

items.name: Poison Arrow
items.description: Watch your prey's health and stamina slowly drain as a result of this deadly arrow.

items.name: Slingshot
items.description: A simple ranged weapon that deals damage from afar.  Better for knocking out a target than killing it outright.  Requires stone to fire.

items.name: Stone Arrow
items.description: Fragments of flint from your stone excavations make up this arrow.

items.name: Torch
items.description: Provides light, and some warmth. Doubles as a melee weapon in a pinch, and can be applied to various saddles for a mobile light source. May draw out nocturnal predators when lit at night.

items.name: Tranq Arrow
items.description: A handy arrow to have in your quiver in any precarious situation. One shot will slow your enemy down to escape...or fight! Beware, this may not work on all dinos!!
